title: For Sale:  Colt Officer's Model .45 ACP
postcontent:
I'm selling my Colt Officer's ACP .45, MK IV, Series 80 Pistol.  It is in the original Colt plastic box, with the instruction book and papers.  The gun is used, but fired very little and is still in like-new condition.  It is all-steel, both slide and frame, with a matte gray durable parkerized finish.  The serial number indicates it was manufactured in 1985.

The Colt Officer’s ACP pistol was introduced in the mid 1980’s to compete in the growing concealed carry market. The full size 1911 with its 5-inch barrel was often too big for concealed carry.   Colt introduced an all-steel copy of the original Colt government with a 3 ½ inch barrel –  1 ½ inches shorter than a full-size Government Model.  Colt also shortened the length of the grip to aid in concealment, dropping the capacity to six rather than the usual seven rounds of 45 ACP.  At the time it was introduced, it was one of the smallest weapons of that caliber. 

The Officer's ACP comes with a functional three-dot sight system and a grip safety that protects the hand.  This gun is prized for its compactness and robust power in  .45 ACP.    The Officer’s  ACP was discontinued in the 1990’s.  They are a piece of Colt history that some people collect just for the nostalgia of it.   As a result, this model is getting very difficult to find.

This would be a perfect concealment pistol for personal, home or automobile security use. How about giving this as an awesome Christmas gift for somebody special. Contact me so we can meet and let you inspect this Colt Officer's ACP .45. I know you won't be disappointed. The price is $795 cash only.  All reasonable offers considered.

This rifle has the usual desired carry wear that most of them display, but appears to have been shot very little. Sights are straight with no cant. Comes with one mag with equal finish wear. This one even had a dirty cleaning kit in the stock when I received it. These forces were often issued US supplied weapons including the DPMS AR 15 and the AK47 Romanian WASR 7.62 x 39. We believe that these rifles were employed by a firm known as SOC USA doing US government security work ( http://www.soc-usa.com/ ) and possibly Ugandan defense contractors shown in the pictures below. The Rifles will show the Flavor of deployment on the battlefield. The guns have a neat a slightly collectable niche for those who may want a conversation piece and good shooter. There were a very limited number of these in the market a few years ago, and they are ALL sitting in collections, you just can't find them. title: For Sale:  New XLP Adams Arms Piston Kit w/Upgraded Complete VDI Low Mass BCG
postcontent:
LNIB AA Piston kit with upgraded complete Voodoo Innovations low mass BCG. I put this on a Short Barrel Rifle and shot a 20 round box of Gemtech 300BLK 187 Subs with it and then traded the upper minus the piston kit to a friend. It comes with the complete AA kit plus the full BCG and a pistol length drive rod, the ID of the gas block is .750"

This design of this piston system is just incredible, especially when shot suppressed. It has 5 different gas settings for numerous applications (ie, subsonic) and is unique in that it can fit under most handguards that use a standard barrel nut, instead of having the block poking up in front of the handguard and disrupting the profile. It also is legitimately self-cleaning, and designed to shoot around 10,000 rounds before requiring to be cleaned. These kits are for a mid-length setup, but pistol, carbine and rifle length drive rods can be purchased separately from Adams Arms to fit whatever length is required.

These run between $360-$380 + s/h + tax depending on where you buy them and that's without the VDI Lifecoat complete bolt that I have. The complete Lifecoat VDI bolts are between $55-$80 before shipping and or taxes. 

Here is the description from AA's website: 

This system will work with .223/5.56 x 45 mm NATO and 300BLK

Kit includes:

Patented One-Piece Low Mass Bolt Carrier
XLP Multi-Adjustable Low Profile Gas Block
Gas Plug
Bushing Installation Rod
Bolt Spring
Drive Rod with Bushing and Spring
Installation DVD
The Adams Arms Piston System:

A short stroke free floating piston system.
Is Self-Cleaning.
Carbon and gases are expelled forward, away from operator.
Corrosive resistant coating processes.
Harmonics are not transferred into the barrel.
Adjustable gas settings for various applications.
Doesn't vent directly to atmospheric pressure; this eliminates flash signature and super sonic crack which is optimal for night vision and suppresses fire.
